# Backend Security Standards

## Input Validation

- Sanitize ALL user input before processing or storing
- Validate request body fields exist and have correct types
- Use parameterized queries / safe JSON operations only

## Authorization

- Every mutating endpoint MUST verify the user's JWT token
- Admin-only routes MUST check `decoded.role === 'admin'`
- Users must only access/modify their own data (prevent IDOR)

## Cookie & Session

- `httpOnly: true` — always, no exceptions
- `secure: true` — required in production
- `sameSite: 'strict'` — required in production
- Never expose tokens in URL parameters or response bodies

## Data Privacy

- Never return `passwordHash` in API responses
- Filter sensitive fields before sending user data
- Log errors server-side only, never expose stack traces to clients
